      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "FLAXLANDS (8) is an honest campaigner who has only missed the top four once in eight career starts and that was in a much tougher Canterbury contest. Gets the reliable Waller/Maloney combination and should be right there when the whips are cracking. SIESTA (1) looked handy saluting at Eagle Farm when resuming and gets a bunch of weight off with the 3kg claim. Solid top three prospects with a repeat of that first-up performance. The well-related ANARITA (3) (full to G2 winner Kristilli) strips fitter third-up from the spell and is drawn to get a soft run from the inside marble. Top three credentials on best figures. MOSAMOUR (6) also hails from a handy family (half to G3 winner Manolo Blahniq) and has won when first-up before. Can run a race while fresh. GAGNANTE ENCHERE (4) is a winner around this circuit who shouldn't be underestimated.",
